  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F).",
    "Combine sweet rice flour and mashed chapssalgaru in a bowl.",
    "Add butter, vegetable oil, ground cumin, salt, and cayenne pepper. Mix until well combined and thick enough to form into balls when dropped from the spoon.",
    "Roll 1 tablespoon dough into small balls. Coat breadcrumbs on both sides of each ball before frying in hot oil for about 2 minutes per side or until golden brown.",
    "Place fried doughballs onto a paper towel-lined plate to drain excess oil, and serve immediately."
